FBIS3-35400 "drnes037_m_94005" FBIS-NES-94-037 Document Type:Daily Report 24 Feb 1994 JORDAN Minister Signs Loan Agreement With U.S. Envoy JN2102205894 Amman Jordan Television Network in English 2000 GMT 21 Feb 94 JN2102205894 Amman Jordan Television Network Language: English Article Type:BFN [From the "News at Ten" program] [Text] Jordan and the United States today signed an agreement under which the United States will finance a Jordanian purchase of 100,000 tonnes of U.S. wheat at a cost of $15 million. The agreement was signed by Finance Minister Sami Qammuh and U.S. Charge d'Affaires Douglas Keene. Mr. Qammuh said the loan will carry 2 percent annual interest for the first seven years and 3 percent thereafter. He said the loan was repayable in 24 installments beginning in the seventh year. Mr. Qammuh said 60 percent of the value of the loan was a grant from the United States to shore up Jordan's budget. The U.S. charge d'affaires said the loan was one aspect of Jordanian-U.S. cooperation.
